Actually thought OP's post was a rightwinger trying to parody leftists. No idea why people almost universally have pre-critical thinking when it comes to psychiatric disease and still think there is some hard border between personality and pathology.

Makes me think of the film Moonrise Kingdom's ending where the entire conundrum was solved by the policeman simply adopting the boy. Sometimes a really hopeless, chaotic situation can just be instantly solved with a slight adjustment. Then suddenly everything will click together.

This is also why Dr. Ray Peat type nutrition ideas like replacing sunflower with coconut oil in the food supply or adopting mass use of T3 in thyroid therapy are so captivating. Knowing a slight adjustment can produce these massive benefits yet it also being so hard to implement.

Most people with hypothyroidism get prescribed T4 only but unless your liver is able to efficiently convert it to T3 you end up not getting the full benefit and then hypothyroidism is generally underdiagnosed

"Iceland is unique in that it is an Anglo-American condominium. The power there is half in the US, and half in the UK. Exactly fifty-fifty. This is the only place on the globe like this, a kind of "no man's land"."

Note that in Orwell's 19 84 the extreme North and Arctic territories are also considered a no man's land grey zone where open fighting between the superpowers continues and there is military action. Then you remember Drumpft's bizarre fiasco with Greenland a few months ago too...

Another example: Bobby Fischer escaped to Iceland. First he went to Japan, but even there the US government could cause him trouble and had him detained, tried to have him extradited back to America, etc. They couldn't touch him in Iceland. He was a free man there. No man's land.
